commitResults.messageTitle: Change command input to be lowercase
commitResults.messageBody:
The original address book does not understand the command when the user types "List" or "DELETE" or "LiSt", etc

The new change converts the input of the command (ie. ONLY the command word eg. "add", "list" and not the rest of the input) to lowercase so that TP can undestand the input even if user types in uppercase
Change command input to be lowercase

In AddressBookParser class, the list command does not check if there are any additonal arguments after the command "list". As such, the students' details would be successfully listed if user input was something like "list all"

Let's add a ListCommmandParser class to check if the user input is valid for the list command (ie. just the word "list"). Else, TP will send a message to user telling the user of the correct format

commitResults.messageTitle: Fix alpha bugs for show and offlinehelp

commitResults.messageBody:
To avoid flagged for overzealous inputs, let's:

* allow up to 4 groups to be tagged to a student

It is possible that one student is in different groups for different examinable components like CA1, CA2)

* do away with restrictions regarding group names

It is possible for students to want to have their own group names that are not e.g. "group 1"

Currently Groups are stored in a hashset within a person

Let's create a separate class to store the groups called GroupList

This is a redundant command.

Let's instead put it together with the default message for invalid commands

The Show Command is unable to work when a student has multiple groups

Let's edit the command such that it is able to work
